%N A390813 a(n) is the size of the largest Sidon subset of the first n positive perfect squares.
%C A390813 A set S is a Sidon set if all sums of the form a + b (where a,b in S and a <= b) are distinct.
%C A390813 Erdős asks if a(n) is n^(1-o(1)) (see Erdős problems link).
%H A390813 Thomas Bloom, <a href="https://www.erdosproblems.com/773">Problem 773</a>, Erdős Problems.
%H A390813 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidon_sequence">Sidon sequence</a>.
%H A390813 <a href="/index/Go#Golomb">Index entries for sequences related to Golomb rulers</a>.
%e A390813 For n = 3, {1, 4, 9} is a subset of {1, 4, 9} with distinct sums 1 + 1 = 2, 1 + 4 = 5, 4 + 4 = 8, 1 + 9 = 10, 4 + 9 = 13, 9 + 9 -> 18 between pairs of elements and no larger set has the required property; so a(3) = 3.
%e A390813 Examples of subsets realizing each largest size are:
%e A390813    1: {1}
%e A390813    2: {1,4}
%e A390813    3: {1,4,9}
%e A390813    4: {1,4,9,16}
